          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The following are equivalent for a deductive system <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>every map is <fr:link href="jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>every map is <fr:link href="jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">thunkable</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>every object is <fr:link href="jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">positive</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>every object is <fr:link href="jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">negative</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>the <fr:strong>cut</fr:strong> law is associative;</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is a precategory.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
